Question:
In a stream, B is between points A and C and equidistant from them. A boat can go from A to B and back in 5 hr 15 min, and from A to C in 7 hr. How long will the boat take from C to A? 
  • Your first attempt
  • Your first attempt
Re-attempt answer
Re-attempt mode: ON
Now You can re-attempt the question
Click here to see the answer now

Your First Attempt Answers

Solution
  • Accepted answer is between: 0 and 0

    • Given:

    Time taken from A to B = 5 hr 15 min.

    Time taken from A to C  = 7 hr

    Concept used:

    Speed upstream is the boat's speed - the stream's speed.

    Speed downstream is the boat's speed + the stream's speed.

    Formula used:

    Speed = Distance/Time

    Calculation:

    Let the distance between A and C be 2x km.

    ∴ Distance between A and B = x km

    Let the Speed of the boat be S km/h and the speed of the water be W km/h.

    According to the question,

    x/(S + W) + x/(S - W) = 5 hr 15 min →(1)

    Again, 2x/(S - W) = 7 hr →(2)

    From (1) × 2 - (2), we get

    ⇒ 2X/(S + W) + 2X/(S - W) - 2X/(S -W) = 10 hr 30 min  - 7 hr

    ⇒ 2A/(S + W) = 3 hr 30 min = 312312 hr

    ∴ Option (4) is the correct answer.

    Was the solution helpful?
